  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "Hark! hark, my soul! angelic songs are swelling O&#39;er earth&#39;s green fields and ocean&#39;s wave\\- beat shore: How sweet the truth those blessèd strains are telling Of that new life when sin shall be no more! Onward we go, for still we hear them sing, &quot;Come, weary souls, for Jesus bids you come&quot;;",
    "v2": "And through the dark, its echoes sweetly ringing, The music of the Gospel leads us home. Far, far away, like bells at ev&#39;ning pealing, The voice of Jesus sounds o&#39;er land and sea, And laden souls, by thousands meekly stealing, Kind Shepherd, turn their weary steps to Thee.",
    "v3": "Faith&#39;s journeys end in welcome to the weary, And Heav&#39;n, the heart&#39;s true home will come at last. Angels, sing on, your faithful watches keeping, Sing us sweet fragments of the songs above; Till morning&#39;s joy shall end the night of weeping, And life&#39;s long shadows break in cloudless love."
  },
